Display Manager does:
Starts graphical environment
Shows login screen
Handles mouse & keyboard
After login:
Starts desktop environment
GNOME / KDE / XFCE
ğŸ‘‰ You see:
ğŸ–±ï¸ Desktop, icons, windows
